>In the April Dr. Dobb's ( page 20 ) it say's that Khufu is
>insecure because the key is only 64 bits long ; I was always
>under the impression that Khufu was 512 bits long ( 64 BYTES ).
>Have I been misinformed?

Khufu has a 64-bit key that is expanded, in a key expansion phase, into
a 512-bit key.

